ion. Illuminating the fault lines both within and beyond the movements of the past and today, this critical book is also hopeful: Duberman urges us to learn from this history to fight for a truly inclusive and expansive society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aGay liberation movementzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aGay rightszUnited StatesxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / General.2bisacsh  aamerican left.  abroad and conservative.  adeep and transformative.  adiscriminatory policies.  aearly gay movement.  aexpansive society.  agender studies.  ahistorians.  ainclusion.  algbtq movement.  algbtq.  anormative inclusion.  aprogress.  aprogressive vision.  aqueer potential.  aradical goals.  ashifts in attitudes.  asocial justice activist.  asocial transformation.  astonewall.  aunited states.  awest.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106676770 cprintz978052029886640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052097084740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520970847423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520970847/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles